Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.06,0:00:10.25,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Nureha...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.90,0:00:15.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Um, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.37,0:00:18.47,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Will you take an escort?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.48,0:02:06.61,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You really saved us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.61,0:02:09.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was just boars, but then \Nwe were attacked by ogres.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.92,0:02:11.36,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No need to thank us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.72,0:02:13.91,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We are adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.30,0:02:17.18,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we save people in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.64,0:02:19.11,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just glad you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.82,0:02:25.87,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, we were saved by that lady, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.53,0:02:31.63,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I really can't take the sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.67,0:02:37.63,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1531,1)}Odyssey Knights
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.95,0:02:35.47,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Odyssey Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.12,0:02:40.76,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,How are you feeling, Roe 2?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.10,0:02:43.82,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, can you close the curtains?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.82,0:02:45.47,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I can't take the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.47,0:02:46.36,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.95,0:02:47.78,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Water?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.17,0:02:49.02,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.02,0:02:49.82,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.46,0:02:55.27,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.27,0:02:59.35,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing... Is that the Celestial Robe?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.35,0:03:01.56,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'm impressed you know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.56,0:03:04.72,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,My teacher wears the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.72,0:03:06.41,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Is he a caster, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.73,0:03:07.56,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.56,0:03:08.95,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,He's an enchanter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.95,0:03:11.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,This robe's pretty high-end gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.77,0:03:14.89,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It has wear-resistance and \Nis good for normal use.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.20,0:03:16.42,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's perfect for long journeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.87,0:03:19.08,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You sound just like Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.01,0:03:24.96,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Um... My teacher's name is Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.96,0:03:27.61,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You sort of remind me of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.12,0:03:32.91,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,So, you're a shrine priestess, and your \Nsubclass is apprentice, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.17,0:03:33.78,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.48,0:03:35.54,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.54,0:03:36.51,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'll heal you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.51,0:03:38.59,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, no need.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.59,0:03:39.36,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.82,0:03:42.05,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,My subclass is vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.57,0:03:44.87,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.10,0:03:48.87,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Vampires are damaged by healing spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.87,0:03:49.55,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.06,0:03:51.87,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.34,0:03:54.78,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Um, what will you do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.17,0:03:59.84,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you come from, Roe 2?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.29,0:04:03.51,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.97,0:04:07.21,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Where did I come from, and where am I going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.72,0:04:10.02,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,A very philosophical question.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.33,0:04:12.52,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not what I meant!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.45,0:04:14.60,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.41,0:04:19.46,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Minori...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.46,0:04:20.36,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.36,0:04:23.49,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you see, during the last battle...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.00,0:04:27.46,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Croissant and Danish weren't hurt, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.46,0:04:28.58,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.03,0:04:29.98,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.98,0:04:32.45,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Items have wear bars, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.45,0:04:34.50,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,If we repair it, can we call them again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.50,0:04:37.41,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,You'd need the woodworking skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.41,0:04:41.31,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We were talking about pushing \Nthe carriage to the next town.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.64,0:04:44.59,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be really bad if more monsters appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.10,0:04:49.07,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,So Tohya says we should escort \Nthe People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.07,0:04:50.10,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.78,0:04:54.60,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you get on the carriage, Rudy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.95,0:04:57.86,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,A sorcerer has more strength than a bard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.86,0:04:58.61,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.15,0:05:01.65,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't want to make a lady do my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.14,0:05:05.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is a big problem, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.03,0:05:09.17,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Monsters that normally live at higher altitudes \Nare coming down to the foothills.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.17,0:05:13.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they're all displacing each \Nother's habitats, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.76,0:05:15.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.19,0:05:19.06,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There's a mountain area called \NBoxurt to the west, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.06,0:05:20.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It has a pretty lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.89,0:05:22.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There are nobles that rule it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.71,0:05:25.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,but supposedly, monsters are \Nshowing up there, also.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.28,0:05:26.71,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Boxurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.71,0:05:27.93,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We're going through it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.93,0:05:28.83,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.83,0:05:30.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you don't need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.59,0:05:33.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Odyssey Knights are over there now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.62,0:05:34.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.62,0:05:35.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They're our heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.18,0:05:38.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They risk their lives to protect \Nus from the monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.88,0:05:40.40,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Heroes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.11,0:05:43.78,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they're like D.D.D. or the Black Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.10,0:05:44.99,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.51,0:05:47.59,Default - italics,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Odyssey... That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.25,0:05:49.24,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,They're a nostalgia faction,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.22,0:05:53.74,HUD1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs18}Flavor Horizon\NSzechuan-style mapo tofu with a sinful flavor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.41,0:05:53.74,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,a group that wants to go home, \Nsometimes called "Odyssey."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.54,0:05:57.87,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,Their goal is to go back to the real world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.32,0:06:00.52,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,But sometimes they go too far
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.52,0:06:03.02,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,and cause trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.18,0:06:08.21,Default - italics,Se,0000,0000,0000,,But he didn't say they were knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.21,0:06:09.79,Default - italics,Se,0000,0000,0000,,They may be someone different.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.28,0:06:16.05,HUD1,Se,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(383,1)\an9}Yuyurugi Village \N{\fs20}Japan Server \NOdawara \NSafe Zone/ No Monsters \NNo PvP \NSkill Use Restricted\NEntry Restrictions/ None\NExit Restrictions/ None
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.61,0:06:13.83,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You saved me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.83,0:06:17.87,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If I'd kept walking under the sun, \NI wouldn't have lasted.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.87,0:06:19.28,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.63,0:06:21.81,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We helped each other out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.05,0:06:23.50,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Here's the food!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.50,0:06:25.89,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,The People of the Land are paying for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.89,0:06:27.44,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,They want to thank us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.63,0:06:28.85,SignB,R,0000,0000,0000,,Soy Sauce
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.16,0:06:29.22,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I want soy sauce!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.11,0:06:31.45,SignB,R,0000,0000,0000,,Worcestershire Sauce
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.68,0:06:30.98,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take Worcestershire sauce.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.98,0:06:31.85,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.74,0:06:34.20,SignB,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Mayo
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.61,0:06:34.80,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Mayo is the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.98,0:06:40.70,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's the cheap, everyday food \Nthat's the best in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.41,0:06:46.17,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Some adventurer, somewhere, \Ncame up with this egg bowl, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.75,0:06:50.74,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,This one's soy sauce, and \Nthat's Worcestershire sauce.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.83,0:06:55.58,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,She's using both?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.58,0:06:58.68,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,The issue of Worcestershire versus \Nsoy sauce is a complicated one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.49,0:07:00.19,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.54,0:07:02.60,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,This thick, black one is Worcestershire sauce,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.60,0:07:04.69,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,and the thick, black one is soy sauce, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.69,0:07:05.70,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.70,0:07:07.69,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,The mayo is good, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.11,0:07:12.32,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, where were you \Nbefore you came here, Roe 2?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.32,0:07:16.50,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I came here from Oou. \NI left about three months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.50,0:07:17.33,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Oou?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:20.11,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,That's where Shiroe went on his expedition.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.11,0:07:23.58,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Before that, I was someplace even farther away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.49,0:07:26.21,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I used castling to get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.48,0:07:27.75,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Castling?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.75,0:07:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.36,0:07:32.26,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's a special spell that lets you \Nchange places with a servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.75,0:07:35.18,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Roe 2 is a summoner, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.18,0:07:41.80,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, Eins's guild, Honesty, has been \Nusing it to investigate the fairy rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.80,0:07:44.47,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You know all kinds of things, Minori!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.13,0:07:47.73,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's just something Shiroe told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.27,0:07:52.11,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Which means you switched \Nplaces with your servant?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.81,0:07:55.30,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if "servant" or "brother" is best.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.30,0:07:57.55,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I know... We'll go with "brother."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.55,0:07:59.12,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I switched places with my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.60,0:08:00.60,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.60,0:08:02.85,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm heading toward Ikoma for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.85,0:08:06.73,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I can't get rid of this vampire \Nsubclass without going there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.73,0:08:09.88,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You can't take any quests to overwrite it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.44,0:08:11.27,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.27,0:08:13.10,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I just have to drop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.10,0:08:16.15,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, how did I end up with this subclass?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.15,0:08:17.89,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I really want to ask the person in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.41,0:08:20.49,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It just changes your appearance!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.49,0:08:22.95,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, it's a little helpful on the moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.95,0:08:25.97,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,but I wish they'd think about what \Nhappens when you're on Earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.97,0:08:28.48,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I can't go on being a vampire!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.26,0:08:30.10,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The moon?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.64,0:08:34.91,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Ikoma's near Minami, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.51,0:08:37.78,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What are we gonna do now, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.14,0:08:42.78,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like we can't repair our \Nsummon flute in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.78,0:08:45.67,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be hard to go on without horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.00,0:08:48.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you just call some horses?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.93,0:08:53.38,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You can call horses, Sis Roe 2?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.10,0:08:56.01,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,"Sis"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.72,0:08:59.46,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Ahem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.88,0:09:03.64,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,W-Would you call me "Sister"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.96,0:09:04.72,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.72,0:09:06.05,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Once more...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.26,0:09:07.05,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.75,0:09:08.60,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.84,0:09:10.15,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Sister Roe 2...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.38,0:09:12.64,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.64,0:09:13.90,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.11,0:09:16.05,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I love it... "Sister"!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.05,0:09:19.41,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,When someone calls me that, \Nit feels like they're relying on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.83,0:09:23.16,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be someone who's \Ntreated like a big sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.16,0:09:25.41,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be loved for being a big sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.11,0:09:30.50,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll accompany you on your \Njourney, and give you horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.82,0:09:34.55,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'll summon you a whole stack of horses, \Nbetter than anyone's ever seen!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.26,0:09:38.76,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,As payment, you'll let me act like a big sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.18,0:09:40.75,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Got it, guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.05,0:09:42.77,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.99,0:09:47.27,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I can't take the sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.56,0:09:52.15,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The water is so nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.15,0:09:55.78,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,They say adventurers don't need baths, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.09,0:09:59.67,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Our wounds heal fast, and we \Nhave self-cleaning functions,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.67,0:10:02.02,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,but it just doesn't feel right without baths, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.73,0:10:04.81,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.81,0:10:08.40,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that Boxurt place \Nwe're going to is a big pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.40,0:10:09.65,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy was saying so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.65,0:10:10.98,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.98,0:10:13.17,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's all part of the adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.45,0:10:14.55,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.94,0:10:17.30,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on with you and Rudy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.89,0:10:19.29,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.29,0:10:21.14,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,He's my puppy, and I go on walks with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.14,0:10:22.44,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.44,0:10:24.56,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You two totally seem like a couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.98,0:10:28.99,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what about you and Nyanta, Serara?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.58,0:10:34.23,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Nyanta's teaching you all kinds of things, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.23,0:10:37.00,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's the stuff you'll need to \Nknow to get married, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.89,0:10:44.87,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Serara, I've got a Marriage Ring that took \Nthirty raids and lots of delicious food.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.87,0:10:47.58,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,You're married to me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.02,0:10:51.58,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,No! It isn't like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.76,0:10:51.58,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.56,0:10:53.98,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.98,0:10:55.59,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, Serara...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.01,0:10:59.70,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,If you act like that, Nyanta will get mad \Nat you when you bathe together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.07,0:11:01.34,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Bathe together?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.78,0:11:04.35,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't the water nice, Serara?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.00,0:11:06.83,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.79,0:11:10.95,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,How are things going with \Nyou and Shiroe, Minori?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.67,0:11:13.73,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,H-How are they going?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.73,0:11:16.17,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing going on with him, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.17,0:11:18.85,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you have a lot of rivals for Shiroe...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.11,0:11:21.32,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.48,0:11:25.20,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, he's the guy who founded the Round Table.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.20,0:11:28.91,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Both Marielle and Henrietta are \Npretty, and friendly with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.91,0:11:31.58,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,And then there's the Tea Party's leader, too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.01,0:11:34.00,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,And also, Akatsuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.00,0:11:37.46,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to get close to my lord, \Nyou must defeat me first!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.13,0:11:41.99,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, isn't Roe 2 \Nwonderful, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.99,0:11:45.34,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, no... {\i1}Sister{\i0} Roe 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.21,0:11:47.90,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-When did you get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.66,0:11:52.48,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Since I'm the big sister, I have physical \Nadvantages over you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.86,0:11:55.51,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, my boobs, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.52,0:11:59.88,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Get a grip, girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.88,0:12:01.86,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Breasts are just for show!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.15,0:12:05.84,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Was that too much for my little sisters?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.07,0:12:09.03,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.36,0:12:10.68,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You look glum.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.68,0:12:11.89,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.89,0:12:15.73,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering what to do for the spring event.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.73,0:12:17.84,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The typical answer would be flower-viewing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.31,0:12:19.48,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Flower-viewing, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.68,0:12:21.30,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.30,0:12:22.67,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.67,0:12:24.38,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone can enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.38,0:12:27.72,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,And that might make everyone friends again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.16,0:12:29.17,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Marie...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.22,0:12:35.22,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Is there really no way for people \Nto be friendly and have fun together?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.58,0:12:45.49,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,And so, it hasn't been a major problem so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.80,0:12:46.68,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.15,0:12:49.05,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Keep at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.25,0:12:50.52,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.52,0:12:57.28,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,But I think you should look at the encounter \Nfrequency in a bit more detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.28,0:12:58.35,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.35,0:12:59.00,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.65,0:13:05.92,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Shiroe\N{\fs18}Log Horizon (Guild Master)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.93,0:13:03.97,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.97,0:13:04.85,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,How do things look there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.26,0:13:05.93,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.44,0:13:09.43,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, nothing major is going on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.77,0:13:12.12,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What about the old chief, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.48,0:13:13.87,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Things seem okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.32,0:13:16.39,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You keep at it, too, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.39,0:13:17.08,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.08,0:13:18.02,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.36,0:13:22.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You tired, Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.60,0:13:24.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's too early for sighing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.16,0:13:28.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There are many problems to discuss, villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.64,0:13:29.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.19,0:13:35.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A major gap is quickly developing here in Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.02,0:13:38.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Those who can develop new \Ntechnology or go hunting
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.30,0:13:41.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the fields are getting richer and richer,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.23,0:13:45.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and those who can't are spending the small \Namount of money they make just to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.77,0:13:48.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.45,0:13:51.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So, what are you trying to say \Nis the cause of this gap?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.27,0:13:56.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,People learning the Teachings and the \Ndevelopment of new items by crafters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.79,0:13:59.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Why are the Teachings a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.10,0:14:02.36,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone can get one if they work hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.95,0:14:05.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't the issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.61,0:14:09.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The large guilds are using their manpower \Nto expand their businesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.83,0:14:12.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We should work to prevent anyone \Nfrom establishing a monopoly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.26,0:14:15.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite the accusation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.30,0:14:18.99,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Honesty's no different, in terms of scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.99,0:14:20.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We don't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.26,0:14:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we haven't gained any Teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.30,0:14:26.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Teachings that each guild has \Nlearned should be made public.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.35,0:14:28.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The same with crafting recipes—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.63,0:14:29.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.77,0:14:32.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's going too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.01,0:14:33.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.70,0:14:37.95,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Since the Apocalypse, making items has \Nbeen a process of trial and error...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.95,0:14:42.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The ramen, soup, figures, the custom carriages.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.02,0:14:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each of those represents a huge time \Ninvestment by a craftsman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.23,0:14:47.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Teachings can only be used by the person
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.87,0:14:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who gained them, so even if we make \Nthem public, there's no point.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.10,0:14:53.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.60,0:14:57.99,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then why don't we confiscate any bank accounts
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.99,0:14:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,above 80,000 gold,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.54,0:15:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and redistribute it to adventurers \Nwith the fewest assets?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.90,0:15:06.17,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That would help the income gap.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.43,0:15:07.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.98,0:15:11.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The money, the Teachings, the recipes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.42,0:15:14.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They all belong to the people who \Nworked hard to get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.32,0:15:17.06,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If we take them, it'd be a huge deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.59,0:15:19.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You know that, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.39,0:15:23.06,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But there are people who \Ncan't adapt to this society.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.49,0:15:25.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Are we just going to abandon them?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.03,0:15:29.11,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we've been holding all these events,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.11,0:15:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to try and make it easier for people \Nto participate, I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.45,0:15:35.91,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That arrogance just keeps them further away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.91,0:15:36.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.03,0:15:40.83,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I w-wasn't trying to be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.19,0:15:42.92,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.30,0:15:46.59,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,If we give these people money and recipes,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.59,0:15:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will they start working hard and happily?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.86,0:15:49.90,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.16,0:15:53.83,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But we cannot just leave them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.83,0:15:56.72,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,If you force people to publicize \Ntheir crafting recipes,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.72,0:15:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that would hurt the engineers' motivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.25,0:16:02.35,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Whenever you're making a recipe, \Nit's a lot of hard work before it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.43,0:16:04.80,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If only Crusty were here at a time like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.78,0:16:07.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.76,0:16:10.50,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I understand your proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.29,0:16:13.83,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And I think some kind of action is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.49,0:16:17.62,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But the Round Table has a finite budget.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.21,0:16:22.62,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't getting money from \Nthe nobles like Minami.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.41,0:16:27.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all see what we can come up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.06,0:16:30.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But if it becomes too late...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.80,0:16:32.25,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in doing this anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.33,0:16:35.16,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If we make a huge decision
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.16,0:16:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like that just among ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.07,0:16:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it could destroy Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.79,0:16:42.76,HUD1,T,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fad(336,1)}Boxurt Mountains \N{\fs20}Boxurt\NField/ Monsters Present \NPVP Permitted \NSkill Use Permitted \NEntry Restrictions/ None \NExit Restrictions/ None
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.90,0:16:47.65,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to Sis Roe 2's horses, \Nwe made it into the Boxurt Mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.06,0:16:49.85,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,but this path is a mess!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.85,0:16:53.15,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Um, in the old world, this was Hakone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.65,0:16:56.39,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Hakone was originally a volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.39,0:16:57.95,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Should I go on ahead?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.95,0:17:01.08,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Visibility is low, and if there are any \Nobstacles in our way, it'll be dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.08,0:17:01.91,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.43,0:17:04.92,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Sulfur, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.31,0:17:06.41,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.41,0:17:07.56,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.56,0:17:09.67,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'll summon you some servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.08,0:17:13.17,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I'm your big sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.38,0:17:14.44,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Servants?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.94,0:17:17.96,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.96,0:17:19.18,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pass...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.57,0:17:21.74,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Then take Wolfie!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.17,0:17:25.02,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.36,0:17:26.69,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get going, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.88,0:17:32.45,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,The sulfur really stinks...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.45,0:17:36.48,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I told you Boxurt wasn't going to be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.18,0:17:40.17,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But the fog's thicker than when \NI last came through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.92,0:17:44.46,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.78,0:17:46.82,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We've still got quite a few...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.82,0:17:47.83,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You guys in trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.62,0:17:50.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Are you adventurers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.31,0:17:51.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Want to buy some swords?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.50,0:17:53.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We have some from levels 10 to 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.31,0:17:54.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They're real treasures, made in Akihabara!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.79,0:17:57.61,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,No, our levels are higher than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.61,0:17:58.68,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.92,0:18:01.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,One of our carriages broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.32,0:18:04.34,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Then push the broken one into the ravine,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.34,0:18:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and pile all you can into the second.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.96,0:18:08.69,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to throw away our cargo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.95,0:18:11.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Would you guys buy them all?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.70,0:18:12.82,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That'd be great.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.82,0:18:14.69,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You two together could afford them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.13,0:18:16.86,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That's crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.86,0:18:19.20,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love to help, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.06,0:18:22.07,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive them, travelers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.27,0:18:27.58,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Since their axle broke, they've spent \Na whole day and night here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.89,0:18:28.61,Green HUD,R,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fad(173,1)}Dariella/ Chronicler
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.97,0:18:30.25,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I know they're rude, but please forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.48,0:18:32.32,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.04,0:18:37.87,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Dariella. I'm a traveling writer. \NA Person of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.87,0:18:39.33,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.33,0:18:41.07,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Rundel Haus Code.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.42,0:18:42.55,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,He's Tohya.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.55,0:18:44.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We're adventurers from Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.04,0:18:46.02,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my. From Akihabara?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.39,0:18:51.27,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Would you be willing to carry some of \Nthese boxes to the fortress ahead?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.79,0:18:56.86,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It would really help the merchants \Nif adventurers were to aid them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.34,0:19:02.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's amazing how strong you are, \Nwith those thin arms!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.77,0:19:04.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Igarashi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.80,0:19:06.21,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's Isuzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.21,0:19:10.92,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Um, this box is filled with goat slimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.94,0:19:14.97,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Some weird guy in Akihabara made us take them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.70,0:19:22.26,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,They ate really fast and passed right out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.26,0:19:26.43,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,They spent a whole night on \Na mountain with monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.43,0:19:28.44,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Of course they're exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.59,0:19:32.57,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you one of the merchants' wives?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.57,0:19:37.71,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,No, I was just riding back to \NMinami on their carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.00,0:19:41.45,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Minami is the same direction as Ikoma, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.88,0:19:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.68,0:19:46.44,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, how about some after-meal tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.44,0:19:47.83,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We have snacks, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.81,0:19:49.83,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Snacks!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.58,0:19:54.34,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,These are Nyanta's special cookies!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.27,0:19:56.42,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,How are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.75,0:19:57.73,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,They're sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.02,0:19:59.21,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,They're very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.83,0:20:03.72,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you all going?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.32,0:20:06.01,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The Redstone Mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.01,0:20:09.83,Default,Re,0000,0000,0000,,I'm heading to Ikoma, but I'm \Ngoing that far with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.13,0:20:11.48,Default,Re,0000,0000,0000,,Because I'm their big sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.90,0:20:13.24,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Big sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.58,0:20:16.48,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You all certainly are young.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.01,0:20:19.49,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Our goal is just beyond the pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.98,0:20:20.80,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.24,0:20:26.25,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But Shiroe said there might be wyverns here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.37,0:20:30.34,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Wyverns are flying monsters, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.34,0:20:33.27,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Their range is spreading.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.27,0:20:36.72,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,As are those of the ogres and other monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.52,0:20:41.67,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.92,0:20:44.39,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Something doesn't feel right, somehow...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.78,0:20:46.26,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming closer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.92,0:20:54.58,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,A raid team?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.58,0:20:56.40,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,They're with
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.29,0:20:58.61,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Plant Hwyaden.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.85,0:20:59.90,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,From Minami!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.15,0:21:04.39,HUD1,I,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fad(402,1)}Shunichi \N{\fs20}Race/ Elf \NGuardian, Lv. 90 \NPlant Hwyaden
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.91,0:21:02.62,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,He's level 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.62,0:21:04.41,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,So are the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.93,0:21:07.90,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,They don't look like PKs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.90,0:21:11.05,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,They're probably the Odyssey Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.17,0:21:15.12,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,The ones protecting the People of the Land?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.12,0:21:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.13,0:21:19.45,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What's that thing they're carrying?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.77,0:21:21.98,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Mobile Temple of Boreas.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.15,0:21:23.91,Location,R,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fad(390,1)}The Mobile Temple of Boreas
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.42,0:21:23.92,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The Mobile Temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.12,0:21:27.18,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I only heard about it on my travels,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.49,0:21:31.93,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,but the Odyssey Knights are taking \Nthem all across the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.76,0:21:37.19,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It immediately revives any adventurer \Nwho loses their life in its vicinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.83,0:21:42.19,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,With that temple, they can revive \Nanywhere and at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.45,0:21:44.50,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,An instant Cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.50,0:21:47.75,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,So the Minami adventurers invented that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.02,0:21:50.85,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But they look so lifeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.62,0:21:53.24,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's like a funeral procession.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.67,0:21:55.62,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It lets you revive anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.93,0:21:58.47,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't know if it's a side effect of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.47,0:22:01.55,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm told it disturbs the voices \Nof adventurers' hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.65,0:22:04.37,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The voices of their hearts?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.42,0:22:11.51,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, that temple is something \Nimportant to you adventurers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.67,0:24:08.88,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,On their journey, they stop at the town of Safil.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.28,0:24:11.09,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,There, Isuzu performs a concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.33,0:24:14.78,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Her melodies entrance the People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.78,0:24:18.99,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Isuzu is happy and exhausted \Nwhen Rudy shares with her
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.36,0:24:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the secrets of this world's music and the \NPeople of the Land's dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.73,0:24:25.84,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: When the Concert Ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.73,0:24:30.94,Title,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,When the Concert Ends
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.33,0:24:27.85,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,I have friends to run with me.
